rces, and ensuring that library catalog meets the needs of all its users. This role is people-focused, requiring individuals to manage learning resources while keeping the library users' needs in mind. The role reports directly to the Provost and works closely with the Degree program teams, Learning Support and Student Life team. RESPONSIBILITIES Curate and maintain library collections to meet the demands of specific user groups Forecast and manage library needs across academic programs Organize and deliver classes, demos, workshops about information resources and help students evaluate reference materials Develop and standardize systems for accessing and distributing library resources Establish and implement library policies and procedures Prepare and administer the budget for the library Maintain records and prepare statistical and analytical reports Stay current with trends and developments by reviewing publications, attending professional events and receiving training from vendors Develop and maintain relationships with external bodies such as vendors and suppliers Promote awareness of research resources, library services and learning opportunities REQUIREMENTS Masters degree in Library Science, Archival Studies, Information Studies or Media Studies Ability to think analytically and to develop new or revised systems, procedures, and workflow In-depth knowledge of computers, the internet, and commercially available library software Conviction on the importance of Information and Digital Literacy Creativity to develop and implement library programs and services Positive attitude toward library users with special needs Ability to motivate, establish and maintain effective working relationships with various stakeholders Ability to communicate both orally and in writing Ability to exercise initiative and independent judgment Relevant work experience in library or information management is a strong plus Apply Now South Africa United StatesCanada ArgentinaAustraliaBelg